According to statistics, between 30% and 75% of the automobiles reported more than once for driving drunk again.
The alcolock would avoid it as it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the rate of alcohol in the breathed air and prevents the start of the car if the driver does not blow abtes; or when a concentration of alcohol is detected is higher than the permitted.
Its cost is more than EUR 1,000 and would be on the account of the sanctioned person.
In this regard, a study conducted in the United States in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with these devices reduce violations by up to 65% during the first year of implantation.
And in Spain it is estimated that it could save the lives of 115 people every year.
The measure is subject to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to address such behaviour before they result in criminal offences.
And to facilitate their implementation, as legal reform can be done by ordinary means, and yet the necessary reform by criminal means requires a reform in an organic law.
The device is not yet available on the Spanish market in any commercial mode, although it has already been piloted in some industrial and public service vehicles.
