The smart car imitates the bee's flight
What would be the best method for developing technologies in order to avoid collisions, if not the imitation of existing obstacles sensors in nature?
For example, that of the bees.
In a surprising project presented at CEATEC in Japan, the bees gave the starting point for Nissan engineers to design the next generation of the collisions prevention system.
The Nissan, in cooperation with the University of Tokyo, designed the automobile robotic steering system of type BR23C imitating nature, to which they gave the characteristics of the bees, with the ultimate objective of creating a system that can avoid all collisions.
During the flight each bee creates its own particular oval space that actually resembles our security protective capsule - he explained in the exhibition Kazuhhiro Doi, technology director of RP and development and research.
They play an important role in the bees' composite eyes that are able to see in all directions at an angle greater than 300 degrees.
To copy the composite eye function, engineers used the laser-ray length measurement system.
This identifies the obstacles ahead of the BR23C within a distance of 2 meters, at an angle of 180 degrees, calculates its distance and sends a signal to the microprocessor of the vehicle that immediately transforms into a manoeuvre to avoid collision.
In a fraction of seconds the obstacle is identified, then the robot of the vehicle imitating the movements of the bees, modifys the direction by rotating the wheels to the extent necessary.
Unlike any existing system today, this manoeuvre is totally instinctive.
"If not, the vehicle robot could not react quickly enough to avoid obstacles," explains Toshiyuki Andoh, head of the Mobility Laboratory and the vehicle robot project.
It must react immediately and instinctively, as this technology corresponds to the most vulnerable inner layer of the safety protective capsule, on a layer within which all types of collisions are currently considered inevitable.
The whole process must reflect what a beekeeper does to avoid other bees.
This process must be done in an open and close eyes.
However, unlike bees, the movement cannot be directed upwards, downwards or diagonal, but can only be two-dimensional and exclusively in the direction of turning wheels
In this way, instead of the infinite possibilities that exist for bees to avoid other bees, here they only used as a possibility for the robot of the car the rotary movement and the acceleration as well as the braking.
The BR23C uses lithium-polymer batteries that are lighter and higher their energy density, meaning that they have a longer lifetime than that of lithium-ion.
According to Andoh, the important thing is the instinctive and intelligent reaction and not the data processing capacity, much less the storage capacity.
This device in every second should only process some input signals and react according to the case.
It is not necessary to store these data or react with an instinctive logic based on data from previous maneuvers, so it uses only a few dozen kilobytes of memory.
No gigabytes or megabytes are needed.
This is the first step in developing technology to immediately avoid obstacles, which according to the calculations of the Nissan, within ten years can be incorporated into serial-made models.
Another possibility for your application is to incorporate the unit into the GPS satellite navigation system to take the driver to your destination, avoiding the obstacles in your path.
You already have a name for this dear boy.
The written version of the $700 billion financial rescue package has been prepared and will be implemented in several phases in order to purchase bad bank credits.
In the first phase, half of the money will be spent.
According to the schedule of the East Coast during the new consultations that lasted until after midnight Saturday, Congress leaders reached an agreement on the financial rescue package of $700 billion in total, after several days of discussion - Reuters reported.
We have made significant progress - said Nancy Pelosi, Democratic President of the North American Congress, stating that it is only necessary to formalize the agreement in a document.
The commitment made to the package was supported by both presidential candidates, Barack Obama and John McCain.
Henry Paulson, Minister of Finance, speaking about the outcome of the compromise, said: this program will work and will be efficient but further measures are needed. According to Pelosi, it is not about saving Wall Street, but about turning the car back to the economy.
The written version of the package was published before the opening of the Asian markets, i.e. on Sunday before 8:00 p.m., according to Washington's schedule (i.e. before two o'clock in the morning of Monday, according to Central Europe's schedule), without causing a spectacular jump in the bags.
On the bill called the emergency law for the economic stabilization of 2008, Monday first will vote for the North American Congress and then the Senate.
President George W. Bush on Saturday night consulted with Pelosi and then the White House also celebrated the news about the agreement.
We are pleased with the progress achieved during the night and highly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy - said Tony Fratto, the spokesman for the White House.
The program is different from the Bush administration's original proposal to spend all the $700 billion to buy securities of bad quality credit funds.
Now only half of the $700 billion can be spent, using $250 billion immediately after Congress votes, probably on Monday, of this sum the Ministry of Finance will buy credit, bad rating securities and the fate of another $100 billion depends on the President's decision.
This programme will be controlled by a special body, in which the President of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The other half of the $700 billion will be spent after a new Congress decision.
According to the law, the Ministry of Finance can apply a combined tactic: it can simultaneously purchase bad credits, mortgages and securities, as well as other "venous" credits as well.
The purchase can be made in auctions or directly - competent persons from the ministry reported.
The law allows the companies concerned to participate in a insurance program where the financial portfolio guarantees the worrying elements, for which companies will pay the amount corresponding to the expected damage.
Henry Paulson stated: the law thus ensures the necessary financial means, which can even reach $700 billion to meet the urgent needs of the American financial system, to deal with the purchase of bad financial means, their insurance or the prevention of risks that could lead to the collapse of some large financial institutions.
We do everything we need to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it - he added.
On the other hand, the heads of the banks who are in trouble and await state aid will be able to count on the official limitation of their compensation, which the American argot simply calls gold parachutes.
Only in certain cases will payments be limited, and the limitations depend on the form of aid from the Ministry of Finance.
The limitation means that if the ministry buys in the framework of an auction, an extra tax will be imposed on gold parachutes, unless the failed head of the bank retires.
By directly buying bad credits, the government will intervene aggressively to ensure that the compensations of the bosses are not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations relate only to new contracts to encourage participation in the programme as well.
This is the first case in American history that will be in force a legal limitation on the revenues of the general directors - this measure commented Democrat Barney Frank, president of the Congress commission, responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares from the banks participating in the programme, thus reducing the risk of taxpayers, as they will ultimately even be able to obtain profits with the transaction as soon as the economy is recovered and with it the bank.
According to the bill in the next five years, the president will have to submit to Congress a proposal on how to return the losses of the financial sector to taxpayers.
Of course, on both sides there were those who expressed their reservations about the project.
This is not what American citizens entrusted us with, that is, the taxpayers' dollars are not being protected - said Republican Congressman of California, Darrell Issa.
Her Democrat colleague from Ohio, Mary Kaptur, said: the measures were prompted by the same ones who are responsible for the collapse of Wall Street.
Industrial prices continue to rise
In August 2008, domestic industrial sales prices increased by 0.1 per cent compared to last month's prices and by 12.9 per cent compared to August 2007's prices - reported by the Central Statistical Office (KSH).
Industrial export prices increased by 1.1 per cent compared to July 2008 and decreased by 3.9 per cent compared to the previous year.
As a result of changes in domestic and export prices, industrial production prices increased by 0.7 per cent over the previous month and by 3.2 per cent over the previous year.
Industrial sales prices increased only to a minimum, with 0.1 per cent.
The domestic sales prices of the processing industry sectors increased minimally, with 0.1 per cent compared to July.
The largest increase in price magnitude occurred in August 2008 in the leather and footwear production sector (2.8 per cent), due first to the increase of 4.6 per cent per month in stock exchanges and belts and the increase of 2.5 per cent in footwear.
The higher price level of plastic and chemical base materials resulted in a significant monthly increase in the prices of the chemical production branch (1.6 per cent).
There was a decrease in price in the petrochemical sector, (1.4 per cent), in the production of electrical machines and instruments (0.9 per cent), as well as - to a minimum measure - in the wood processing sectors (0.1 per cent).
The prices of paper manufacture, publishers and printers did not change.
In the rest of the processing industry, prices increased between 0.2 and 0.9 per cent.
In the supply of electricity, gas, heat and water which represent a significant weight within domestic trade, an increase of 0.3 per cent was recorded in August, first as a result of the effect of the increase in official prices from 1 July.
In a 12-month comparison - in domestic sales of processing industry sectors - the highest price increase was recorded in the petrochemical sector (32.4 per cent).
In the metal processing sector, an increase of 13.2 per cent was observed, while in the food, beverage and tobacco industry, with a determining weight, there was an increase of 11 per cent.
There was a decrease in prices in the textile industry (2.5 per cent), as well as in the manufacture of electrical machines and instruments (0.3 per cent).
In the other processing sectors the rate of price growth was between 0.6 and 9.1 per cent.
Over the past year in the processing industry, prices globally increased by 10.2 per cent.
The prices of electricity, gas, heat and water supply exceeded the prices of the previous year by 18.7 per cent.
In August, among the different sectors of domestic trade, the largest monthly price increase (0.7 per cent) was recorded in the sectors of investment goods.
In the sectors of consumer goods, prices increased by 0.3 per cent, in the prices of the energy sector and in the intermediary sectors there were no changes compared to the previous month.
In August 2008, with respect to the same month of the previous year, the highest price increase occurred in the energy sectors and in the intermediary industry (16.8 per cent).
In the manufacturing branches of consumer goods there was a decrease of 6.8 per cent and investment goods 1.4 per cent.
The export prices of the industry calculated in HUF increased by 1.1 per cent compared to the previous month, and compared to 12 months, there was a decrease of 3.9%.
The quotation of our national currency in one month was reduced by 1.7 per cent over the euro and by 7.1 per cent over the dollar, compared to August 2007 it strengthened by 7.5 per cent over the euro and 15.9 per cent over the dollar.
